The paper deals with graph similarity search, which is a common operation in graph databases. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (Database) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to estimate Graph Edit Distance (GED) efficiently, which involves probabilistic modeling. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new graph similarity measure called Graph Branch Distance (GBD), which can be efficiently calculated in polynomial time. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments conducted on real and synthetic data sets, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of graph similarity search in computer vision applications, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
